BACILLARY DYSENTERY - BURUNDI
*****************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Cholera - Burundi (03) 970404175750
Date: Sat, 29 Nov 1997 23:21:22 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>
Source: Panafrican News Agency

BUJUMBURA, Burundi
Thousands of cases of bacillary dysentery have been reported in several
areas of Burundi since early November, according reports from provincial
doctors.
The most affected is the northeastern province of Muyinga, where the health
officer
there, Dr Cyprien Ntembagara reported 1,200 cases in October.
Between Nov. 10-25, the southeastern province of Makamba registered 50
deaths out
of the 500 cases reported at hospital. Some 110 cases were reported in
Bujumbura,
the capital.

--
